    <r3d:description language="eng">BAID is a suite of online, interactive maps and services that support Arctic science with a special focus on the research hubs of Barrow, and surrounding areas on the North Slope of Alaska. In 2000 the BAID project began as a Microsoft Access database which was used to centralize information about research plots mapped with BASC&#039;s new DGPS system. Today BAID includes the locations of over 10,000 research plots and instrument locations dating back to the 1940s.</r3d:description>
